Eldoret South police boss Richard Omanga said the nine-seater Mololine Safari Sacco  matatu was en route to Eldoret  town when it hit the lorry  from behind. The lorry  was delivering cement to  a construction site in Eldoret town. According to Omanga, the driver of the ill-fated matatu was fatigued and drowsy when the accident occurred adding that earlier, he had made several trips to and from Nakuru. “The driver sustained injuries and is recuperating at Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital. The other passengers suffered  minor injuries and were rushed to the same hospital, treated and discharged,” he said.